            "__cdata": "<p class=\"p_20\">15. A 30 year old man who was recently started on haloperidol 30 mg/day developed hyperpyrexia, muscle rigidity, akinesia, mutism, sweating, tachycardia and increased blood pressure. The investigations showed increased WBC count, increased creatinine phophokinase. These are no history of any other drug intake or any signs of infection. The most likely diagnosis is:</p>"
